er (phone 13800138000) with user 6. However, it does NOT insert any messages. So
when the E2E user logs in, they will see a conversation list with one conversati
on (with user 6, nickname `TestUser6`), but no messages. The chat page will be e
mpty.\n\nThe existing `enter_chat.yaml` flow only asserts the chat page and inpu
t field are visible. It doesn\'t send a message.\n\nThe missing coverage is:\n1.
`im/send_message.yaml` - enter chat, type a message, send it, assert it appears.
\n2. Maybe `im/receive_message.yaml` - but this requires another user sending a 
message, which is hard in E2E without a second device or backend API call.\n3. M
aybe `im/read_receipt.yaml` - also hard.\n\nBut the task says "Bug Fix" and "≤3 
个文件". Maybe the fix is just to add the `send_message.yaml` flow and update th
e seed script to include a system welcome message (so the chat isn\'t empty). Or
maybe we need to fix the seed script to insert messages.\n\nWait, the review rep
ort mentioned: "匹配成功时自动插入系统欢迎消息". The `MatchingService` emits `ma
tch:created` event, and `ImService.handleMatchCreated` creates a system message.
But the seed script inserts matches directly into the DB, bypassing the service.
So there are no system messages in the seeded conversations.\n\nFor E2E tests, t
he conversation list will show the match, but when entering chat, there will be 
no messages. The chat page loads messages via API. If there are no messages, the
list is empty. To test sending a message, we can just type and send, and assert 
the bubble appears.\n\nBut there might be a bug: The `ChatPage` uses `SwChatMess
ageList` which might not have a semantics identifier for the message bubbles, ma
king it hard for Maestro to assert. Let\'s check `SwChatMessageList`.',
